Eicher Motors is a leading Indian automotive company that owns Royal Enfield motorcycles and has joint ventures with Volvo and Polaris. It produces trucks, buses, motorcycles and will soon produce personal vehicles. Royal Enfield is the oldest motorcycle brand in continuous production and has experienced strong growth in recent years. Eicher's joint ventures support its operations in commercial vehicles and personal transportation.
